 The Ndigbo Unity Forum (NUF), a pan-Igbo socio-political pressure group, has called on the South-East governor to fulfill their pre-election promises to the people. The President of NUF, Mr. Augustine Chukwudum, made the call in a statement on Monday in Enugu. Chukwudum noted that most of the five states in the zone are still lagging behind in development despite the 20 years of uninterrupted civilian rule. He said: “Moving from one state to the other especially in rural areas, you will see death traps called road as well as school building without toilets. Continue reading Group urges South East governors to fulfill pre-election promises at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard The President of NUF,  Augustine Chukwudum, gave the commendation while speaking in Enugu shortly after INEC declared the result on Sunday . A group, Ndigbo Unity Forum (NUF), has commended President Muhammadu Buhari for ensuring free and fair governorship election in Anambra. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Gov.… November 20, 2017 In "News" By Jonathan Nda- Isaiah, Abuja and Obinna Ogbonaya, Abakaliki President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday assured Igbo people that his administration will ensure the timely execution of roads, power and other projects in the South East. Addressing leaders of thought and traditional rulers at a meeting in Government House, Abakiliki when he… November 14, 2017 In "News" Augustine Chukwudum, President, Ndigbo Unity Forum (NUF), a pan-Igbo socio-cultural group, has urged Ndigbo to vote wisely by voting for the re-election of President Muhammadu Buhari. Chukwudum made their views known while speaking with newsmen on Tuesday in Enugu. He enjoined Ndigbo all over the country to vote en mass… January 2, 2019 In "News"